<div class="whales__header">
  <div class="whales__header__container">
    <div class="whales__header__container__signature">
      Whales by <span> Icalia Labs</span>
    </div>
    <div class="whales__header__container__half">
      <div class="whales__header__container__logo">
        <%= image_tag('whales-logo-white.svg') %>
      </div>
      <div class="whales__header__container__text">
        The easiest way to dockerize your applications
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="whales__header__container__half">
      <%= react_component("LandingApp", props: state, prerender: false) %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="whales__files">
  <div class="whales__files__dockerfile">
    <pre>
      <code class="dockerfile"></code>
    </pre>
  </div>
  <div class="whales__files__dockercompose">
    <pre>
      <code class="yaml"></code>
    </pre>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="whales__star-us">
  <div>
    <%= image_tag 'small-belugas.png' %>
    Make the Belugas happy :)
  </div>
  <div>
    <a href="https://github.com/Gueils/whales">
      <i class="fa fa-github fa-2x" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      <span>Star us on Github</span>
    </a>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="whales__description">
  <%= image_tag 'belugas-container.svg', class: 'whales__features__item__container' %>

  <div class="whales__features__item__title">
    Dockerize your apps in a breeze
  </div>

  <div class="whales__description__content">
    Dockerizing your apps was never this easy.
    We present to you the <span>Whales</span> ecosystem: a
    set of tools to automatically dockerize
    your applications.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="whales__features">
  <div class="whales__features__item">
    <%= image_tag 'belugas-analyzer.png', class: 'whales__features__item__analyzer' %>

    <div class="whales__features__item__title">
      Belugas Analyzer
    </div>

    <div class="whales__features__item__content">
      Whales uses analizers to detect multiple features
      in your project based on a code static analysis.
      Thanks to these analyzers we can detect which language,
      framework, database, and dependencies your project uses.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="whales__features__item">
    <%= image_tag 'belugas-files.png', class: 'whales__features__item__files' %>

    <div class="whales__features__item__title">
      Usage
    </div>

    <div class="whales__features__item__content">
      By default, Whales returns a Dockerfile and a Docker
      Compose file. These are what you need to run Docker
      on development mode. You can also obtain a Dockerfile
      for production if needed.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="whales__contribute">
  <a href="https://www.github.com/Gueils/whales">
    <i class="fa fa-github fa-2x" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    <span>Contribute on Github</span>
  </a>
</div>

